 Mbizana police have arrested a sangoma and found a human head and private parts suspected to belong to the schoolgirl found murdered, with her body dismembered, two weeks ago.

The arrest early on Friday follows the suspected muti killing of Sinoyolo Mgaga, 18, an AB Tshayingca High School Grade 10 pupil, of KwaNikhwe.


Police arrested the 30-year-old sangoma at his home at KwaNikhwe.
He led police to a grave where a head and private parts were exhumed, police said.


